<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-763-141  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 763 141.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  July 17 1989 v6 n28 p31(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Plotters provide increased speed without price hike. (Zericon'sZ3000 printed at 7- to 10-inches-per-second; the Z4000 offers15-ips performance) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kovsky, Steven.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Zericon Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Zericon Designer Z3000 (plotter) (product introduction)Zericon Designer Z4000 (Plotter) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     PlottersProduct IntroductionColorCost ReductionPerformance Improvement.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Plotters Provide Increased Speed Without Price HikeandM;FREMONT, Calif.andP;  -- Zericon claims it has doubled the performance of its penplotters without any accompanying price increase.andM;Zericon's new Designer Series plotters, models Z3000 and Z4000, operate at 15inches per second (ips), compared with the 7- to 10-ips range of previousplotters, a company spokeswoman said.andM;The Designer Series plotters feature ergonomic styling, which eases the taskof loading largesized paper, she said.andP;  A menudriven LCD readout panel hasalso been included in the models.andM;Model Z3000 handles paper sizes that range from 8-1/2 by 11 inches to 24 by36 inches.andP;  The Z3000 is priced at $2,695.andM;Model Z4000 handles paper sizes as large as 36 by 48 inches.andP;  It is priced at$2,995.andP;  Both models will be available Aug. 15, and an optional multiple-penpackage will be available in October for $450, the spokeswoman said.andM;The prices are identical to those for Zericon's existing plotter line, sheadded.andM;According to Zericon President Gary Zera, more economical manufacturing andfactory-direct-shipping practices reduced costs, making it possible to avoidprice increases for the new products.andM;Zericon Inc. is located at 40491 Encyclopedia Circle, Fremont, CA 94538,(415) 490-3906.andO;</TEXT></DOC>